{
    "esm": "0.4.0",
    "metadata": {
        "name": "SurfaceRunoffInfiltration",
        "description": "Surface runoff and infiltration for the pervious-road urban surface, following Oleson et al. (2010, CLM Tech Note Ch. 5) §5.2, Eqs. 5.49-5.57. Migrated from UrbanCanopy.jl@9200edd4 src/hydrology.jl:384 (`SurfaceRunoffInfiltration` @component). Implements the SIMTOP-based (Niu et al., 2005) runoff partition with frozen-soil-modulated saturated fraction (Eqs. 5.50-5.51), a maximum infiltration capacity built from top-layer matric-potential and saturation (Eqs. 5.52-5.55), and snow-aware surface infiltration (Eqs. 5.56-5.57). Observed-only: all 14 inputs are parameters and the seven outputs (f_frz_1, f_sat, s, v, q_infl_max, q_over, q_infl) are given by algebraic equations.",
        "tags": [
            "urban_canopy",
            "hydrology",
            "surface-runoff",
            "infiltration",
            "simtop",
            "observed-only",
            "clmu"
        ],
        "created": "2026-05-12T00:00:00Z",
        "authors": [
            "UrbanCanopy.jl contributors",
            "EarthSciModels migration (esm-ds0b)"
        ],
        "references": [
            {
                "citation": "Oleson, K. W., et al. (2010). Technical Description of version 4.0 of the Community Land Model (CLM). NCAR Technical Note NCAR/TN-478+STR. Chapter 5 (Hydrology), Section 5.2 (Surface Runoff and Infiltration), Eqs. 5.47-5.58, pp. 124-128."
            },
            {
                "citation": "Niu, G.-Y., Yang, Z.-L., Dickinson, R. E., & Gulden, L. E. (2005). A simple TOPMODEL-based runoff parameterization (SIMTOP) for use in global climate models. Journal of Geophysical Research, 110, D21106."
            }
        ]
    },
    "models": {
        "SurfaceRunoffInfiltration": {
            "reference": {
                "notes": "source_ref: UrbanCanopy.jl@9200edd4f15609f20339d3a7d104de8064544310:src/hydrology.jl:384\nUpstream `SurfaceRunoffInfiltration` is an MTK `@component` whose 14 inputs (q_liq_0, q_seva, f_max, z_v, k_sat_1, B_1, ψ_sat_1, θ_liq_1, θ_sat_1, θ_ice_1, w_ice_1, w_liq_1, Δz_1, has_snow) are `@parameters` (driven by a parent column/atmosphere/soil-hydraulics coupler) and whose seven outputs (f_frz_1, f_sat, s, v, q_infl_max, q_over, q_infl) are time-indexed `@variables` with seven algebraic equations and no derivatives. Identical structure preserved here.\n\nThe upstream component declares six `@constants` (α=3.0 [dimensionless], f_over=0.5 [m^-1], θ_imp=0.05 [m^3/m^3], ρ_liq=1000.0 [kg/m^3], one_kgpm2=1.0 [kg/m^2], zero_kgpm2s=0.0 [kg/(m^2*s)]). Per the convention of sibling files in this directory (snow_compaction.esm, groundwater_drainage.esm), `@constants` are promoted to parameters here with the upstream default values so the seven equations reference them by name without re-injecting magic numbers. The two `_kgpm2` / `_kgpm2s` constants exist upstream purely to make the unit-bearing `max()` floors well-typed under DynamicQuantities; they preserve unit-consistency of the equation AST and are kept here for round-trip fidelity.\n\nThe upstream component declares no defaults on the 14 input `@parameters`. The canonical Python runner (`earthsci_toolkit.simulation.simulate`) requires concrete numeric defaults to instantiate the system in isolation, so defaults are seeded from a mid-range CLMU pervious-road state representative of Oleson 2010 Tables 5.1-5.2: sandy-loam top layer (k_sat_1=1e-5 m/s, B_1=5.0, ψ_sat_1=-0.05 m, θ_sat_1=0.4 m^3/m^3, Δz_1=0.02 m), moderate water table (z_v=2.0 m), f_max=0.4 (mid-range maximum saturated fraction), zero precipitation/evaporation, and no snow. Each test below overrides the inputs that exercise its specific branch.\n\nObservability classification: this component is functionally observed-only — all seven outputs are given by single algebraic equations in terms of the parameters (the `(t)` time index has no role since there are no derivatives). Test scenarios use `time_span: [0, 1]` and sample at t=0 to mirror the convention used by the other observed-only ESM files in this directory (aquifer_water_balance.esm, impervious_water_balance.esm, snow_compaction.esm).\n\nEquation-ordering note (vs upstream comment ordering): the upstream Julia source orders the equations as (5.51, 5.50, 5.53, 5.54, 5.52, 5.49, 5.56-5.57). The same numerical order is preserved here verbatim because the AST is dependency-driven (each equation references only earlier outputs and the 14 inputs) and the canonical Python runner topologically sorts before solving — so ordering is informational, not load-bearing.\n\nTolerance rationale (model-level rel=1e-9): observed-only algebraic system (no ODE integration); the longest equation chain is O(10) IEEE-754 float64 operations including two `exp()` calls in f_frz_1 (each carrying ≈1 ULP of relative error) — worst-case roundoff is ~10*ULP ≈ 1e-15. 1e-9 leaves seven orders of magnitude of headroom above ULP roundoff and is well below any plausible physical-discrimination scale on the surface-water flux densities (typical CLMU q_liq_0 / q_over / q_infl values fall in the 1e-6 to 1e-2 kg/(m^2*s) range). Tests that yield exact algebraic zeros use `abs: 1e-15` to bypass the relative-tolerance singularity at zero."
            },
            "tolerance": {
                "rel": 1.0e-9
            },
            "variables": {
                "q_liq_0": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "kg/(m^2*s)",
                    "default": 0.0,
                    "description": "Liquid water reaching surface from rain or snowmelt"
                },
                "q_seva": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "kg/(m^2*s)",
                    "default": 0.0,
                    "description": "Surface evaporation of liquid water"
                },
                "f_max": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 0.4,
                    "description": "Maximum saturated fraction (Eq. 5.50, dimensionless)"
                },
                "z_v": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m",
                    "default": 2.0,
                    "description": "Water table depth (Eq. 5.50)"
                },
                "k_sat_1": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m/s",
                    "default": 1.0e-5,
                    "description": "Saturated hydraulic conductivity of top soil layer"
                },
                "B_1": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 5.0,
                    "description": "Clapp-Hornberger exponent for top soil layer (dimensionless)"
                },
                "ψ_sat_1": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m",
                    "default": -0.05,
                    "description": "Saturated matric potential for top soil layer (typically negative)"
                },
                "θ_liq_1": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m^3/m^3",
                    "default": 0.2,
                    "description": "Volumetric liquid water content of top soil layer"
                },
                "θ_sat_1": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m^3/m^3",
                    "default": 0.4,
                    "description": "Porosity of top soil layer"
                },
                "θ_ice_1": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m^3/m^3",
                    "default": 0.0,
                    "description": "Volumetric ice content of top soil layer"
                },
                "w_ice_1": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "kg/m^2",
                    "default": 0.0,
                    "description": "Ice content of top soil layer"
                },
                "w_liq_1": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "kg/m^2",
                    "default": 50.0,
                    "description": "Liquid water content of top soil layer"
                },
                "Δz_1": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m",
                    "default": 0.02,
                    "description": "Thickness of top soil layer"
                },
                "has_snow": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 0.0,
                    "description": "Whether snow layers are present (1=yes, 0=no, dimensionless)"
                },
                "α": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 3.0,
                    "description": "Scale-dependent parameter for frozen fraction (Eq. 5.51, dimensionless)"
                },
                "f_over": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m^-1",
                    "default": 0.5,
                    "description": "Decay factor for saturated fraction (Oleson 2010 p. 126)"
                },
                "θ_imp": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m^3/m^3",
                    "default": 0.05,
                    "description": "Minimum effective porosity floor for relative-saturation denominator (Oleson 2010 p. 127)"
                },
                "ρ_liq": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "kg/m^3",
                    "default": 1000.0,
                    "description": "Density of liquid water (Oleson 2010 Table 1.4)"
                },
                "one_kgpm2": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "kg/m^2",
                    "default": 1.0,
                    "description": "Unit mass per area, used to unit-balance the 1e-10 floor in the f_frz_1 max() guard"
                },
                "zero_kgpm2s": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "kg/(m^2*s)",
                    "default": 0.0,
                    "description": "Zero flux sentinel, used to unit-balance the max() floors in q_over and q_infl"
                },
                "f_frz_1": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "1",
                    "description": "Impermeable fraction from frozen soil (Oleson Eq. 5.51, dimensionless)"
                },
                "f_sat": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "1",
                    "description": "Fractional saturated area (Oleson Eq. 5.50, dimensionless)"
                },
                "s": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "1",
                    "description": "Relative saturation of top soil layer (Oleson Eq. 5.53, dimensionless)"
                },
                "v": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "1",
                    "description": "Infiltration variable v (Oleson Eq. 5.54, dimensionless)"
                },
                "q_infl_max": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "kg/(m^2*s)",
                    "description": "Maximum infiltration capacity (Oleson Eq. 5.52)"
                },
                "q_over": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "kg/(m^2*s)",
                    "description": "Surface runoff (Oleson Eq. 5.49, SIMTOP)"
                },
                "q_infl": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "kg/(m^2*s)",
                    "description": "Infiltration rate (Oleson Eqs. 5.56-5.57; snow-aware)"
                }
            },
            "equations": [
                {
                    "lhs": "f_frz_1",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "/",
                        "args": [
                            {
                                "op": "-",
                                "args": [
                                    {
                                        "op": "exp",
                                        "args": [
                                            {
                                                "op": "*",
                                                "args": [
                                                    { "op": "-", "args": [0.0, "α"] },
                                                    {
                                                        "op": "-",
                                                        "args": [
                                                            1.0,
                                                            {
                                                                "op": "/",
                                                                "args": [
                                                                    "w_ice_1",
                                                                    {
                                                                        "op": "max",
                                                                        "args": [
                                                                            { "op": "+", "args": ["w_ice_1", "w_liq_1"] },
                                                                            { "op": "*", "args": [1.0e-10, "one_kgpm2"] }
                                                                        ]
                                                                    }
                                                                ]
                                                            }
                                                        ]
                                                    }
                                                ]
                                            }
                                        ]
                                    },
                                    {
                                        "op": "exp",
                                        "args": [
                                            { "op": "-", "args": [0.0, "α"] }
                                        ]
                                    }
                                ]
                            },
                            {
                                "op": "-",
                                "args": [
                                    1.0,
                                    {
                                        "op": "exp",
                                        "args": [
                                            { "op": "-", "args": [0.0, "α"] }
                                        ]
                                    }
                                ]
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "lhs": "f_sat",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "+",
                        "args": [
                            {
                                "op": "*",
                                "args": [
                                    { "op": "-", "args": [1.0, "f_frz_1"] },
                                    "f_max",
                                    {
                                        "op": "exp",
                                        "args": [
                                            {
                                                "op": "*",
                                                "args": [-0.5, "f_over", "z_v"]
                                            }
                                        ]
                                    }
                                ]
                            },
                            "f_frz_1"
                        ]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "lhs": "s",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "max",
                        "args": [
                            {
                                "op": "/",
                                "args": [
                                    {
                                        "op": "-",
                                        "args": [
                                            {
                                                "op": "/",
                                                "args": [
                                                    "θ_liq_1",
                                                    {
                                                        "op": "max",
                                                        "args": [
                                                            "θ_imp",
                                                            { "op": "-", "args": ["θ_sat_1", "θ_ice_1"] }
                                                        ]
                                                    }
                                                ]
                                            },
                                            "f_sat"
                                        ]
                                    },
                                    {
                                        "op": "max",
                                        "args": [
                                            { "op": "-", "args": [1.0, "f_sat"] },
                                            0.01
                                        ]
                                    }
                                ]
                            },
                            0.0
                        ]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "lhs": "v",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "/",
                        "args": [
                            { "op": "*", "args": ["B_1", "ψ_sat_1"] },
                            { "op": "*", "args": [0.5, "Δz_1"] }
                        ]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "lhs": "q_infl_max",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "*",
                        "args": [
                            "ρ_liq",
                            "k_sat_1",
                            {
                                "op": "+",
                                "args": [
                                    1.0,
                                    {
                                        "op": "*",
                                        "args": [
                                            "v",
                                            { "op": "-", "args": ["s", 1.0] }
                                        ]
                                    }
                                ]
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "lhs": "q_over",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "+",
                        "args": [
                            { "op": "*", "args": ["f_sat", "q_liq_0"] },
                            {
                                "op": "*",
                                "args": [
                                    { "op": "-", "args": [1.0, "f_sat"] },
                                    {
                                        "op": "max",
                                        "args": [
                                            "zero_kgpm2s",
                                            { "op": "-", "args": ["q_liq_0", "q_infl_max"] }
                                        ]
                                    }
                                ]
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "lhs": "q_infl",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "ifelse",
                        "args": [
                            { "op": ">", "args": ["has_snow", 0.5] },
                            { "op": "-", "args": ["q_liq_0", "q_over"] },
                            {
                                "op": "max",
                                "args": [
                                    {
                                        "op": "-",
                                        "args": [
                                            { "op": "-", "args": ["q_liq_0", "q_over"] },
                                            "q_seva"
                                        ]
                                    },
                                    "zero_kgpm2s"
                                ]
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                }
            ],
            "tests": [
                {
                    "id": "all_zero_inputs",
                    "description": "Null state — every input zero except f_max=0 (drives saturation pathway off) and the mid-range soil defaults that do not zero out the denominators in s. All seven outputs are exactly zero by IEEE-754: f_frz_1=0 because w_ice_1=0 with finite w_liq_1; f_sat=0 because (1-f_frz_1)*0*exp(0)+0=0; s=0 because θ_liq_1=0; v=0 because ψ_sat_1=0; q_infl_max=0 because k_sat_1=0; q_over=0 because q_liq_0=0; q_infl=max(0-0-0, 0)=0. Exercises the additive/multiplicative-zero limits of all seven equations.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "q_liq_0": 0.0,
                        "q_seva": 0.0,
                        "f_max": 0.0,
                        "z_v": 0.0,
                        "k_sat_1": 0.0,
                        "B_1": 0.0,
                        "ψ_sat_1": 0.0,
                        "θ_liq_1": 0.0,
                        "θ_sat_1": 0.4,
                        "θ_ice_1": 0.0,
                        "w_ice_1": 0.0,
                        "w_liq_1": 50.0,
                        "Δz_1": 0.02,
                        "has_snow": 0.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "f_frz_1",    "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0, "tolerance": { "abs": 1.0e-15 } },
                        { "variable": "f_sat",      "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0, "tolerance": { "abs": 1.0e-15 } },
                        { "variable": "s",          "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0, "tolerance": { "abs": 1.0e-15 } },
                        { "variable": "v",          "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0, "tolerance": { "abs": 1.0e-15 } },
                        { "variable": "q_infl_max", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0, "tolerance": { "abs": 1.0e-15 } },
                        { "variable": "q_over",     "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0, "tolerance": { "abs": 1.0e-15 } },
                        { "variable": "q_infl",     "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0, "tolerance": { "abs": 1.0e-15 } }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "dry_quiescent",
                    "description": "Dry-soil quiescent state — no precipitation, no evaporation, no ice, moderate liquid storage. With q_liq_0=0 and q_seva=0, q_over and q_infl must both be exactly zero regardless of the saturated-fraction state. f_sat reaches the typical CLMU mid-range value (0.4·exp(-0.5·0.5·2) = 0.2426 at f_max=0.4, z_v=2 m), s settles at 0.34, q_infl_max takes its unsaturated value (0.175 kg/(m^2*s) — the upper-bound infiltration capacity in the absence of forcing).",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "q_liq_0": 0.0,
                        "q_seva": 0.0,
                        "f_max": 0.4,
                        "z_v": 2.0,
                        "k_sat_1": 1.0e-5,
                        "B_1": 5.0,
                        "ψ_sat_1": -0.05,
                        "θ_liq_1": 0.2,
                        "θ_sat_1": 0.4,
                        "θ_ice_1": 0.0,
                        "w_ice_1": 0.0,
                        "w_liq_1": 50.0,
                        "Δz_1": 0.02,
                        "has_snow": 0.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "f_frz_1",    "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0, "tolerance": { "abs": 1.0e-15 } },
                        { "variable": "f_sat",      "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.2426122638850534 },
                        { "variable": "s",          "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.3398361550389345 },
                        { "variable": "v",          "time": 0.0, "expected": -25.0 },
                        { "variable": "q_infl_max", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.17504096124026639 },
                        { "variable": "q_over",     "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0, "tolerance": { "abs": 1.0e-15 } },
                        { "variable": "q_infl",     "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0, "tolerance": { "abs": 1.0e-15 } }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "moderate_rain_unsaturated",
                    "description": "Typical rainfall event on an unsaturated pervious-road column: q_liq_0=1e-4 kg/(m^2*s) (~0.36 mm/hr) with no evaporation, no ice, no snow. Because q_liq_0 << q_infl_max (1e-4 vs 0.175), the infiltration-excess branch of q_over (the max() second term) is exactly zero; only the saturation-excess term contributes: q_over = f_sat·q_liq_0 = 0.2426·1e-4 = 2.43e-5. q_infl = q_liq_0 - q_over - q_seva = 7.57e-5 — the standard partition into saturation-area runoff and column infiltration.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "q_liq_0": 1.0e-4,
                        "q_seva": 0.0,
                        "f_max": 0.4,
                        "z_v": 2.0,
                        "k_sat_1": 1.0e-5,
                        "B_1": 5.0,
                        "ψ_sat_1": -0.05,
                        "θ_liq_1": 0.2,
                        "θ_sat_1": 0.4,
                        "θ_ice_1": 0.0,
                        "w_ice_1": 0.0,
                        "w_liq_1": 50.0,
                        "Δz_1": 0.02,
                        "has_snow": 0.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "f_frz_1",    "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0, "tolerance": { "abs": 1.0e-15 } },
                        { "variable": "f_sat",      "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.2426122638850534 },
                        { "variable": "s",          "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.3398361550389345 },
                        { "variable": "v",          "time": 0.0, "expected": -25.0 },
                        { "variable": "q_infl_max", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.17504096124026639 },
                        { "variable": "q_over",     "time": 0.0, "expected": 2.426122638850534e-05 },
                        { "variable": "q_infl",     "time": 0.0, "expected": 7.573877361149466e-05 }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "fully_saturated_surface",
                    "description": "Surface fully saturated (f_max=1, z_v=0 ⇒ f_sat = (1-0)·1·exp(0)+0 = 1). The Eq. 5.49 SIMTOP partition collapses to q_over = q_liq_0 (all rain becomes saturation-area runoff; the infiltration-excess term is multiplied by 1-f_sat=0). q_infl = q_liq_0 - q_over - q_seva = 0 — no water infiltrates through a fully saturated surface. Also exercises the max(1-f_sat, 0.01) floor in s: with 1-f_sat=0, the floor activates at 0.01, and combined with θ_liq_1=θ_sat_1 the s expression reaches exactly 0 (because θ_liq/θ_sat - f_sat = 1 - 1 = 0).",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "q_liq_0": 1.0e-3,
                        "q_seva": 0.0,
                        "f_max": 1.0,
                        "z_v": 0.0,
                        "k_sat_1": 1.0e-5,
                        "B_1": 5.0,
                        "ψ_sat_1": -0.05,
                        "θ_liq_1": 0.4,
                        "θ_sat_1": 0.4,
                        "θ_ice_1": 0.0,
                        "w_ice_1": 0.0,
                        "w_liq_1": 50.0,
                        "Δz_1": 0.02,
                        "has_snow": 0.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "f_frz_1",    "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0, "tolerance": { "abs": 1.0e-15 } },
                        { "variable": "f_sat",      "time": 0.0, "expected": 1.0 },
                        { "variable": "s",          "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0, "tolerance": { "abs": 1.0e-15 } },
                        { "variable": "v",          "time": 0.0, "expected": -25.0 },
                        { "variable": "q_infl_max", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.26 },
                        { "variable": "q_over",     "time": 0.0, "expected": 1.0e-3 },
                        { "variable": "q_infl",     "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0, "tolerance": { "abs": 1.0e-15 } }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "fully_frozen_top_layer",
