                {
                    "id": "partial_ice_water_mix",
                    "description": "Partially-frozen top layer (w_ice_1=20, w_liq_1=30 ⇒ ice fraction = 0.4): exercises the intermediate branch of Eq. 5.51 where f_frz_1 ∈ (0, 1). f_frz_1 = (exp(-3·(1-0.4))-exp(-3))/(1-exp(-3)) = 0.1216. f_sat then blends frozen and SIMTOP contributions. With θ_liq_1=0.1 and θ_sat_1-θ_ice_1=0.3, the saturation ratio θ_liq_1/0.3 ≈ 0.333 falls just below f_sat ≈ 0.335 ⇒ the max(..., 0) floor on s activates (the numerator is a tiny negative number; max() clamps it to 0).",
