                {
                    "id": "infiltration_excess_runoff",
                    "description": "Infiltration-excess (Hortonian) runoff regime: clay-like top layer (k_sat_1=1e-8 m/s) under intense rainfall (q_liq_0=5e-3 kg/(m^2*s) ≈ 18 mm/hr). q_infl_max collapses to 1.75e-4 ≪ q_liq_0, activating the second term of Eq. 5.49: q_over = f_sat·q_liq_0 + (1-f_sat)·(q_liq_0 - q_infl_max) = 0.2426·5e-3 + 0.7574·(5e-3 - 1.75e-4) = 4.87e-3. Nearly all rain becomes runoff; only 1.33e-4 infiltrates (close to q_infl_max). This is the canonical CLMU clay-soil storm scenario complementary to fully_saturated_surface (which exercised the saturation-excess limit).",
